import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['x'], data['y'], label='Data Points')
    plt.xlabel('X')
    plt.ylabel('Y')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between X and Y?')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['x'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='X Distribution')
    plt.axvline(data['x'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['x'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('X')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of X?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
